-- query.promql --
aws_alb_request_count_sum
-- seed --
CREATE TABLE otel_metrics_histogram (
    MetricName String,
    Attributes Map(String, String),
    ResourceAttributes Map(String, String),
    TimeUnix DateTime64(9),
    Count UInt64,
    Sum Float64
) ENGINE = MergeTree ORDER BY (MetricName, Attributes, TimeUnix);
CREATE TABLE otel_metrics_sum (
    MetricName String,
    Attributes Map(String, String),
    ResourceAttributes Map(String, String),
    TimeUnix DateTime64(9),
    Value Float64
) ENGINE = MergeTree ORDER BY (MetricName, Attributes, TimeUnix);
CREATE TABLE otel_metrics_gauge (
    MetricName String,
    Attributes Map(String, String),
    ResourceAttributes Map(String, String),
    TimeUnix DateTime64(9),
    Value Float64
) ENGINE = MergeTree ORDER BY (MetricName, Attributes, TimeUnix);
INSERT INTO otel_metrics_gauge VALUES
    ('aws_alb_request_count_sum', map('load_balancer', 'app/web/abc'), map(), toDateTime64('2026-01-01 00:00:00', 9), 4096);
-- expected_rows --
[
  ["aws_alb_request_count_sum", {"load_balancer": "app/web/abc"}, "2026-01-01T00:00:00Z", 4096]
]
-- description --
Regression pin for the schema-report (2026-06-16) bug: a STANDALONE
GAUGE whose MetricName ends in `_sum` (or `_count`) returned 0 series
because the PromQL->CH name resolution routed the suffix exclusively to
the histogram-companion (bare-name) + sum (suffixed) tables and never
scanned the gauge table where the row actually lives.

Real-world source: yace (yet-another-cloudwatch-exporter) emits each
CloudWatch statistic as a name suffix — `aws_applicationelb_request_count_sum`,
`*_average`, `*_p99` — all as plain gauges. Pre-fix, every `_sum`/`_count`
stat metric was invisible to the Prometheus query API (request-rate +
error-rate panels on the "AWS / Load Balancers" dashboard painted empty),
though the rows sat in `otel_metrics_gauge`.

The fix adds a GAUGE arm (literal suffixed name) to the `_count`/`_sum`
companion union: histogram(bare) UNION sum(suffixed) UNION gauge(suffixed).
Here the histogram + sum tables are empty and only the gauge holds
`aws_alb_request_count_sum`, so the gauge arm is the only one that returns
a row — exactly the path that was missing. A genuine histogram companion
(see histogram_sum_basic.txtar) still resolves via the bare-name arm; its
extra gauge/sum arms are cost-free empties under the MetricName PREWHERE.
